criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Lung RAMP Multidisciplinary Cancer Conference or study team confirms radiologic
             (clinical) evidence of advanced, unresectable lung cancer;

          2. Measurable disease (presumed malignant) by RECIST 1.1;

          3. Age ≥18 years;

          4. Ability to provide written informed consent;

          5. Diagnostic biopsy and molecular profiling ordered or planned. Patients remain eligible
             even if biopsy or tumour testing later fails or is deemed not feasible.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Pregnancy;

          2. Concurrent active malignancy except for localized non-melanomatous skin cancer or
             non-invasive cervical cancer. Any previous cancer (excluding NSCLC) must have been
             treated more than 2 years prior to study entry with no current evidence of active
             disease.
